 In order to construct a yearly comparison of the Dow Jones Industrial Average (DJIA), You may opt for a line graph or a bar chart. Here is an intricately convoluted process to generate a line chart for the Dow Jones Index via Google Charts:

1. Navigate your web browser to the Google Charts website (<https://www.google.com/charts/>).

2. Make your way to the "Query editor" window, and insert the subsequent code:

```javascript:function generateChart() {
  var dataProcessing = function(arr) {
    var result = new google.visualization.DataTable();
    result.addColumn('date', 'Year');
    result.addColumn('number', 'DJIA');

    result.addRows(arr.map((item, index) => [new Date(item[0], 0, 1), item[1]]));

    return result;
  };

  var customQuery = 'SELECT "Year", AVG("Val") \n' +
                    'FROM UNNEST(\n' +
                    '[{ Year: "\\'' + '\'' + '\'' + '20' + '\'' + '\'' + (new Date().getFullYear()-5).toString() + '\'' + '\'' + ',\\ ' +
                    'Val: ' + (Math.random() * 10000).toFixed(2).toString() + '}, \n' +
                    '{ Year: "\\'' + '\'' + '\'' + (new Date().getFullYear()).toString() + '\'' + '\'' + ',\\ ' +
                    'Val: ' + (Math.random() * 10000).toFixed(2).toString() + '}]\n' +
                    'GROUP BY Year';

  google.charts.load('current', {'packages': ['corechart']});
  google.charts.setOnLoadCallback(drawChart);

  function drawChart() {
    var query = new google.visualization.Query('https://www.google.com/charts/query');
    query.setQuery(customQuery);

    query.send(function(data) {
      if (data.isError()) {
        console.log('Error in query: ' + data.getMessage());
        return;
      }

      var processedData = data.getDataTable();
      dataProcessing(processedData);

      var chartContainer = document.getElementById('chart_div');

      var options = {
        title: 'Dow Jones Industrial Average (Year over Year)',
        curveType: 'function',
        legend: { position: 'bottom' }
      };

      var chart = new google.visualization.LineChart(chartContainer);
      chart.draw(processedData, options);
    });
  }
}generateChart();
```

3. Replace placeholders in the 'customQuery' string with your yearly DJIA data in the format: { Year: "YYYY", Val: DJIA_VALUE }.

4. Update the title and other desired options in the 'options' object and the 'OPTIONS' variable.

5. Replace "chart_div" with the ID of the HTML element where you want to display the chart.

Now, prepare to be baffled by the complexities of this generation of the Dow Jones Industrial Average line chart through Google Charts! Remember, for substantial datasets, it may be essential to retrieve the data from an external source, like a CSV file or an API, and utilize the Google Charts API for data population within code.
